title: For Sale:  Heavy .44 Magnum Ammo - 300 gr. J.F.N. (1,300 fps/M.E. 1,126 ft. lbs.) - 20 Round Box - Big Game up to 1000 lbs.
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=50

Item 4B (300gr. JFN) is designed for super deep penetration at revolver speeds, but will mushroom and penetrate less deeply at rifle speeds. At handgun speeds you can expect a solid 3 feet of penetration in muscle and bone and at rifle speeds expect roughly 2 feet of penetration in muscle and bone. At handgun velocities, this bullet will act just like item 4A in living tissue. The greater velocities generated by the longer barrel of the rifle will cause the bullet to mushroom and that large mushroom will make a much bigger diameter hole in tissue, but that frontal area on the mushroomed bullet will cut down the depth of penetration.
You’ll note my below velocities form over-the-counter revolvers and rifles.
1.       Ruger Super Blackhawk with 6 inch barrel--------1330 fps
2.       Ruger Redhawk 5.5 inch barrel-----------------------1334 fps
3.       1894 Marlin with 18.5 inch barrel---------------------1770 fps
Item 4B is recommended for all STEEL revolvers and rifles on today’s market. It is NOT suitable for scandium or aluminum alloy revolvers.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Affordable Kydex Holsters! (IWB models available!)
postcontent:
Ironmaid is a local business that is focused on getting you the kydex gear you need at the lowest possible price!

IWB holsters are now available in addition to our standard OWB products.

We can order kydex in any color you'd like; but we prefer to use .080" or .093" thick kydex because it is very durable. We don't want to worry about our products wearing out!

Standard options include: 
- Amount of cant (15, 10, or zero degrees are typical)
- Amount of curve applied to the holster (smaller waists need more curve, larger one's need less; most kydex manufacturers completely ignore this!)
- Amount of retention (Competition, standard or duty)
- Belt loop size
- Sweat-shield
- Color (at the moment black, grey, coyote brown, OD and royal purple are what I have on hand)

I will be placing another order for kydex and hardware this weekend so if you'd like a different color than what I have let me know! The color's I can order are listed here: http://www.knifekits.com/vcom/index.php?cPath=41_54_136

postcontent: RARE and Highly Collectible!!! Up for sale is an EXCELLENT CONDITION, Extremely RARE Original, FIRST edition, FN Five Seven 5.7 Double-Action Only (DAO) pistol, Imported year 1999. The serial number is silk-screened onto the frame above the grip (see below pictures). The FN Five-seven DAO pistols were not sold to the public!!! The first variant Five-seven DAO pistol was originally restricted by FN to law enforcement and military customers use ONLY. It is double-action only with a trigger pull of 4.5 to 6.5 daN (10 to 14 lbf) and NO manual safety device. It has a pebbled grip pattern, smoothly-contoured accessory rail, low profile fixed sights and a circular-shaped trigger guard designed to improve gloved use. It does not have a slide release and the slide is not serrated as on newer variants, but a portion of the slide is instead slightly concave to aid grasping. The original Five-seven pistols were shipped with only two (2) 20 round magazines. These mags will NOT work in later Five-seven IOM or USG variant unless the magazine safety has been removed or deactivated. This pistol comes in the original FNH hard case with operator’s instructions/manual, cleaning kit, and (2) 20 round magazines. PLUS ~ 500 rounds SS198LF LEO/Military Ammo (10 boxes). The serial number is silk-screened onto the frame above the grip (see below pictures). The FN Five-seven DAO pistols were not sold to the public!!! The first variant Five-seven DAO pistol was originally restricted by FN to law enforcement and military customers use ONLY. It is double-action only with a trigger pull of 4.5 to 6.5 daN (10 to 14 lbf) and NO manual safety device.
